syllabus /ˈsɪləbəs/

(syllabuses) 

1. N-COUNT A syllabus is an outline or summary of the subjects to be covered in a course. 教学大纲 [美国英语] 

例： The course syllabus consisted mainly of novels by African-American authors, male and female. 该课程的教学大纲主要包括了非裔美国男女作家的小说。 

2. N-COUNT You can refer to the subjects that are studied in a particular course as the syllabus . 课程 [英国英语]

